 Susan Richey-Schmitz 123RF.comIn terms of the new legislation by the Taiwanese parliament, the consumption, purchase or possession of dog and cat meat is outlawed. Offenders face a fine of up to 250,000 Taiwanese dollars. The same Bill has increased the penalty for illegally or cruelly killing an animal, or abusing an animal to a maximum two-year jail term and a fine of up to 2-million Taiwanese dollars. Although it has been argued that the consumption of dog meat has diminished in Taiwan, there have been confirmed reports of dog meat for sale recently.